  "prompt": "How was your experience at the Global Citizen India Festival 2016?",
  "response": "I don't have personal experiences or attend events, but I can provide information about the Global Citizen India Festival 2016. The event took place on November 19, 2016, in Mumbai at the MMRDA Grounds. It was a significant event aimed at promoting global issues such as education, equality, and sustainability.\n\nThe festival featured performances by prominent artists, including Coldplay, Jay Z, Demi Lovato, and several Indian artists like A. R. Rahman, Arijit Singh, and Shankar-Ehsaan-Loy. Additionally, the event included appearances by Bollywood celebrities like Shah Rukh Khan, Amitabh Bachchan, and Priyanka Chopra, who supported the cause and engaged with the audience.\n\nThe festival was part of the Global Citizen movement, which encourages people to take actions to improve the world and rewards them with tickets to the event. Overall, it was a high-energy and impactful event that combined entertainment with social activism.",
